1. PROJECT BACKGROUND & STRATEGIC VISION
1.1 Project Context
The Department of Forests seeks to modernize its offense reporting and monitoring mechanism
by replacing manual, paper-based workflows with a secure, digital, and data-driven system. The
objective is to ensure timely reporting, accountability, transparency, and real-time
intelligence across all forest ranges.
1.2 Proposed Solution – T-FOMS
Vidyayatan Technologies proposes the Telangana Forest Offense Management System
(T-FOMS), modeled on the Crime and Criminal Tracking Network & Systems (CCTNS) used
by Police Departments.
T-FOMS will function as the central nervous system for forest offense reporting and
monitoring, digitizing the “first response” workflow from field to headquarters.
1.3 Key Objectives
● Standardization: Digitization of Preliminary Offense Reports (POR) across all ranges
● Accountability: Biometric login and geo-fenced reporting
● Real-time Intelligence: Live dashboards for DFOs, Rangers, and PCCF
2. SCOPE OF WORK
2.1 Component A – Mobile Application (“The Digital Lathi”)
Target Users: Forest Guards / Beat Officers
Platform: Android (Native / Flutter)
Features:
1. Offline Store-and-Forward Architecture for deep forest areas
2. Voice-to-Text AI for dictation and structured POR creation
3. Mandatory GPS (Lat/Long) & Timestamp Capture
4. Restricted Media Upload – live camera capture only
5. Biometric Login (Fingerprint / Face ID)
2.2 Component B – Admin Command Portal (“The HQ”)
Target Users: DFOs, Rangers, PCCF
Platform: Web-based (ReactJS)
Features:
1. Live Kanban Dashboard (Reported → Verified → Charge Sheet → Closed)
2. Automated PDF Generation of PORs & Seizure Lists (Govt formats)
3. GIS Heatmaps for offense hotspot visualization
3. TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE
Layer Technology
Frontend ReactJS (Web), Flutter (Mobile)
Backend Java Spring Boot
Database PostgreSQL + PostGIS
Infrastructure Docker / Kubernetes
AI Services Python Microservice (Voice-to-Text)
The architecture is enterprise-grade, scalable, and compliant with government
e-Governance standards.
